WALK TO THE BEACH FROM CAPITOLA KNOLLS! Single-level upstairs condo with your own large private deck overlooking nature. Adorable home that is move-in ready and waiting for you to put your own personal touches on. Gorgeous and well-maintained landscaped park-like setting with lush green grasses with a community pool and spa to enjoy. Desirable location...walk to Capitola Village, Gayle's Bakery, restaurants, shopping, schools or jump on Hwy 1 right around the corner. Easy access to all of the best beaches including Seacliff, Rio Del Mar,
Manhattan Beach, & Santa Cruz. You'll never want to leave this gem, so come see it now! $...535,000 2/1.5 Single level Upstairs Condo 3 Bedrooms 2 bathrooms (no showers) Private Deck Sqft 1163 Parking 1 Garage Unit Cash Only.

EXAMPLE: Address, City, County, Zip Code; Square Feet, Number of Bedrooms, Number of Bathrooms, Number of Parking Spaces, Special Features, Property Description. We use TensorFlow, BERT, and GPT-2 to retrieve additional features such as house attributes, local amenities, etc.

Our approach consists of three main stages:

\begin{enumerate}
\item Feature Extraction - Pretraining models (BERT, GPT-2, TensorFlow) using a large dataset to extract various features.
\item Feature Pooling - Using Feature Extraction models to feed to a classification model using a specific pre-defined feature weighted scheme to form a feature pool.
\item Prediction - Predict the category of the property according to the feature pool formulated.
\end{enumerate}

Using the above approach, our preliminary results show average accuracy results of about 80\%, as compared to baselines of around 60\%. Our future work includes fine-tuning our models with the limited amount of real estate listing data available, and comparing the results with publicly available benchmark datasets.

We also conducted an experiment to test the performance of the feature extraction models when no pre-trained models were used. Since we had a limited amount of data available, therefore, we used a random forests classifier with varying numbers of decision trees, ranging from 100 to 1,000 trees. The results show that using even the random forests with low numbers of decision trees can perform as well or even better than BERT and GPT-2 models that achieved higher accuracy scores. The experiment also showed that utilizing a feature pooling strategy with a specific weighted feature scheme can further improve predictions when compared to baselines where no preprocessing was attempted.

\begin{figure}[h]
\centering
\includegraphics[width=\columnwidth]{imgs/features-weight.png}
\caption{Various feature weights tested on a random forests model with trees of varying sizes. The predicted class was determined by the average weight of each feature.}
\label{fig_4}
\end{figure}

Our final goal is to combine the feature extraction techniques with a real estate listing management system, where the system will be capable of receiving a real estate listing request, extracting features, and predicting the property category based on the extracted features.

We hope that our work can contribute to addressing the problems faced by real estate agents that can be automated to achieve greater efficiency, while improving the user experience in property searches. This is just the beginning of our work, and we hope to gain more insights as we progress in the field.

\section{Conclusion \& Future Work}

In this chapter, we addressed the challenges faced when using artificial intelligence to automate real estate services that involve the understanding of complex textual input. We introduced the problem statement, motivation and discussed the background and current state of the art research related to this problem. We conducted an experiment to demonstrate the effectiveness of a pre-trained BERT model on the task of text classification, and presented the results of our model in comparison to the traditional approach of using a random forests model. We concluded this chapter by proposing future directions for our research, which include developing a more robust training dataset, and further exploring our use case with respect to automated property listing.

