$Ballpark$ = the range of scores that are appropriate to assign to a restaurant by the author.

$Predict$ = the prediction by the author that the restaurant will receive a score in the range of $Ballpark$.

$Scores$ = the scores that Yelp assigns to restaurant reviews.

\noindent {\bf Task Description:}$\:$ Given a Yelp review and its corresponding score, predict how many stars the author will give to the restaurant, based on the following assumptions:
\begin{itemize}
\item[1] The lower bound on the author's score range is $Ballpark$.
\item[2] The upper bound on the author's score range is not greater than $Ballpark + 1$.
\item[3] The author's score for the review is given by the sum of $Ballpark$ and the number of points by which the score deviates from the predicted score.
\end{itemize}

\noindent {\bf Example:}$\:$

\begin{code}
Ballpark:  3 stars

Review: "The food was mediocre. The service was ok, not great, but not the worst. The bread was very good. I ordered the muscle fries. They had a sweet Vidalia onion flavor. No need for fries bc they were soggy wo much flavor. My boyfriend ordered a pesto chicken pasta and it was again mediocre. The pesto bc was not strong and there was not enough sauce for both the chicken and pasta. We ordered a side of mac n cheese.. again it was not creamy and not good. My dessert was great. I got a brownie sundae. It was huge. I ended up not eating it all."

Predicted score: 2.5 stars

Final Score:  3 stars
\end{code}

\begin{itemize}
\item The score is estimated based on the following assumptions:
\begin{itemize}
\item $Ballpark = 3$, the author's score range is [1 star - 3 stars]
\item $Ballpark + 1 = 4.5$ stars, the upper bound on the author's score range is not greater than 4.5 stars.
\end{itemize}
\item The review score is estimated based on the following calculation:
\begin{itemize}
\item The review score is assigned by adding $Ballpark$ points.
\item The deviation from the predicted score is 1.5 stars to account for the difference between the author's range of score and the range of scores assigned to Yelp reviews.
\end{itemize}
\item The final score is estimated based on the following calculation:
\begin{itemize}
\item The final score is assigned by adding the author's score range and the score deviation.
\end{itemize}
\end{itemize}

